---
import Content from '~/components/widgets/Content.astro';
import Hero from '~/components/widgets/Hero.astro';
import Layout from '~/layouts/PageLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Retinopathy of Prematurity',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Hero Widget ******************* -->
  <Hero
    image={{
      src: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-CEEhmAGpYzE?crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&ixid=MnwzNjUyOXwwfDF8c2VhcmNofDgzfHxwcmVtYXR1cmV8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjE3NTIzMjAw&ixlib=rb-1.2.1&q=80&w=1080',
      alt: 'Baby holding wooden cube',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="title" class="text-center text-4xl font-bold text-blue-600">
      Retinopathy of Prematurity
    </Fragment>
  </Hero>

  <!-- Content Widget - What is Retinopathy of Prematurity? **************** -->
  <Content
    isReversed
    title="What is Retinopathy of Prematurity?"
    items={[
      {
        description:
          '• Retinopathy of Prematurity (ROP) is a potentially blinding condition that affects premature infants. It occurs when abnormal blood vessels grow in the retina, which is the light-sensitive part of the eye.',
      },
      {
        description:
          '• This disorder is primarily seen in infants born before 32 weeks of gestation or weighing less than 2.75 pounds at birth. ROP can lead to retinal detachment and permanent vision loss if not diagnosed and treated early.',
      },
      {
        description:
          '• Timely screening and intervention are crucial for preventing severe outcomes, but early detection remains a challenge, particularly in areas with a shortage of trained specialists.',
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1519389950473-47ba0277781c?ixlib=rb-4.0.3&ixid=M3wxMjA3fDB8MHxwaG90by1wYWdlfHx8fGVufDB8fHx8fA%3D%3D&auto=format&fit=crop&w=2070&q=80',
      alt: 'Colorful Image',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <!-- Content Widget - Understanding Diagnosis Codes **************** -->
  <Content
    isReversed
    title="Understanding Diagnosis Codes"
    items={[
      {
        description:
          '• ICD-10 Code: The International Classification of Diseases, 10th Edition, is the most commonly used system for coding diseases and medical conditions. It is used worldwide for health insurance billing, diagnosis, and research.',
      },
      {
        description:
          '• E-Code: This code identifies external causes of injury and poisoning. It helps to record circumstances of accidents, such as falls or burns, and is used for statistical purposes.',
      },
      {
        description:
          '• Z-Code: These codes are used to identify factors that may influence a patient\'s health status but are not a disease or injury. They can include things like family history or lifestyle factors.',
      },
      {
        description:
          '• CPT Code: The Current Procedural Terminology (CPT) code system is used for identifying medical, surgical, and diagnostic procedures, commonly for billing purposes in the U.S.',
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1521747116042-5c5c2ab5c6d9?crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&ixid=MnwzNjUyOXwwfDF8c2VhcmNofDg0fHxwcmVtYXR1cmV8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjE3NTIzMjAw&ixlib=rb-1.2.1&q=80&w=1080',
      alt: 'Diagnosis Codes Image',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <!-- Content Widget - The Problem and How We Can Help **************** -->
  <Content
    isReversed
    title="The Problem and How We Can Help"
    items={[
      {
        description:
          '• Early detection of Retinopathy of Prematurity (ROP) is crucial to prevent vision loss, but many areas lack the necessary expertise and infrastructure for proper screening.',
      },
      {
        description:
          '• Delayed or improper diagnosis can result in permanent damage to the retina, leading to loss of vision in infants who may not be treated in time.',
      },
      {
        description:
          '• Lack of awareness and access to trained specialists limits the early detection of ROP, especially in low-resource regions.',
      },
      {
        description:
          '• Our platform provides an easy and efficient way for hospitals and healthcare providers to screen and track ROP cases, offering support through AI-driven analysis.',
      },
    ]}
    image={{
      src: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1556740738-b6a63e27c4df?crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&ixid=MnwzNjUyOXwwfDF8c2VhcmNofDk2fHxwcmVtYXR1cmV8ZW58MHx8fHwxNjE3NTIzMjAw&ixlib=rb-1.2.1&q=80&w=1080',
      alt: 'Help and Support Image',
    }}
  >
    <Fragment slot="bg">
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-blue-50 dark:bg-transparent"></div>
    </Fragment>
    <Fragment slot="footer">
      <div class="text-center mt-4">
        <a href="/uploadastro" class="bg-blue-500 text-white px-6 py-2 rounded">
          Upload Your Data
        </a>
      </div>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

  <!-- Content Widget - Contact Us for Any Support **************** -->
  <Content
    isReversed
    title="Contact Us for Any Support"
    items={[
      {
        description:
          '• If you have any questions or need assistance, feel free to reach out to us via email. Our team is here to support you every step of the way.',
      },
    ]}
  >
    <Fragment slot="footer" class="text-center mt-4">
      <a href="mailto:support@ropplatform.com" class="text-blue-600 underline">
        support@ropplatform.com
      </a>
    </Fragment>
  </Content>

</Layout>
